url.description: The URL to send the request to.

method.description: The HTTP method to use for the request.

baseURL.description: The base URL to be used in requests.

headers.description: HTTP headers to be sent with the request.

params.description: URL parameters to be sent with the request.

data.description: The data to be sent as the request body.

timeout.description: The number of milliseconds before the request times out.

withCredentials.description: Indicates whether or not cross-site Access-Control requests should be made using credentials.

responseType.description: Indicates the type of data that the server will respond with.

maxContentLength.description: Specifies the max number of bytes for the content of the request.

validateStatus.description: Defines whether to resolve or reject the promise for a given HTTP status code.

maxRedirects.description: The maximum number of redirects to follow in node.js.

socketPath.description: The UNIX socket to be used in node.js.

proxy.description: Proxy configuration to use for the request.

cancelToken.description: A cancel token that can be used to cancel the request.
